[h1]The Crimson Bath[/h1]

An ancient rite, half-remembered and half-feared. A captive of your dungeons gives up their blood; you take back the years. Each affliction undone demands its own sacrifice.

[h2]What it does[/h2]
Adds a single player-only decision, [b]The Crimson Bath[/b], available to a ruler who carries one or more old-age maladies and holds at least one young captive.

[list]
[*] Each malady undone (infirm, clouded eyes, faltering heart, fragile bones, withering mind) costs one prisoner under thirty.
[*] The rite brands the doer a witch.
[*] Adds 25 stress.
[*] Five-year cooldown.
[/list]

The AI will not use this decision.

[h2]Compatibility[/h2]
[b]CK3 1.19.[/b] Adds one new decision. Touches no vanilla files. Safe to add or remove mid-save.
